accumulate shares at the low end of my value range and then have inventory to
peel off shares when the company gets back in the higher end of their valuation
zone. I do notice that if some news is released on their unregulated business
(ie. Oil discovery, spin off rumors), you get a pop in the parent company.
That's where I usually will let a few shares go as over time, the price drops
back down.

